cs.CR, cs.DB, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.DS 

This paper deals with privacy concerns in Location-based Services (LBS), which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the problem of finding the optimal anonymization for LBS logs, which involves data management and optimization (cs.DB). The use of historic user trajectories and log anonymization policies also suggests a connection to machine learning and data mining (cs.SI, cs.LG). Finally, the paper describes an algorithm for trajectory-aware anonymization, which involves computational complexity and algorithm design (cs.DS).
